<br>
While I love being able to enchant my own metals, clay, and mithril, distill and thicken and purify my own mana, imbue my own raw diamonds, and do all of the other pre-combines that require various skills to do before the FINAL combine....<br>
<br>
...when someone else expects me to do it for them it becomes a pain in the neck.<br>
<br>
I think every combine I've done has been different.  Everyone brings different parts for different combines, in assorted levels of assembly.  For some reason, I rarely have problems with brewing, baking, or pottery.  I can't recall a time when anyone has failed to bring all parts for the combines, for which I am INTENSELY grateful, and I love doing those combines, and would do for free all day long just for that reason.<br>
<br>
JC, however, is in some kind of weird class of its own, maybe for the reason I stated at first.  Since PoP JC combines require a raw diamond to be imbued, a vial of distilled mana to be created, and a brick to be smithed with said distilled mana, it's almost impossible for a character to bring all the parts, ready to go, for the final combine.  I understand this.  I'm even willing to go out on a ledge and say that if they at least brought me all the parts for all the precombines, I wouldn't have too much of an issue with it, even though that's actually 2 spells and 2 combines, not just one click.<br>
<br>
What gets gnarly is when they don't have the sapphires or the mana vial for the distilled mana.  I think that has got to be my biggest pet peeve.  <br>
<br>
I hate stopping whatever it is Im doing to go get them for the person needing the combine.  And yet, that is faster that trying to explain what they need.  I have hotkeys explaining it.  I spell it out.  I tell them to consult their LoY maps.  I tell them the name of the vendor, the loc, and the exact position of the building relative to any other building in the zone.  And they STILL can't find the F'ing parts.  Or the vendor.  Or the building.  Or they can't figure out how to use locs.  Or they can't use their compass.  Or they don't have LoY and so no maps.  Or whatever.<br>
<br>
How can you put so much time/money into an item and not know EXACTLY what you need, or where to get it?  Too many people rely on the combiner to babysit them through their combine...a combine for which they do not donate...and then scream bloody murder if said combiner is so selfish to ask for a little kick back.<br>
<br>
Getting mighty sick of people telling me how selfish I am when I ask for compensation for my time.  KEI, combines, imbues, enchantments...hell I even have a project froglok sideline going for people to check faction.<br>
<br>
Still no plat love for the chanter.<br>
<br>
And people say all chanters are rich.  Bah humbug! <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.familjenguild.com/dspMember.php?Name=Hildie"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.familjenguild.com/images/logo/hildie.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I am now an NPC. When you hail me, I will say, &quot;Greetings. I can [buff] you, [imbue gems], [enchant] items, or [combine] goods for you to sell.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=novbre>Novbre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:green;'>Tavern Patron</span></span><br>  Posts: 104<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(4/30/03 3:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3222.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/djimon/myhomepage/small%20sig%20final.jpg?mtbrand=AOL_US WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> LOL This from the woman who giggles over the mayhem her 100pp for kei /ooc's cause.<br>
